A review comment was posted on pull request #{{ pr_number }} in {{ repository }}.

Reviewer: {{ reviewer }}
Comment: {{ review_comment }}

Review branch: {{ branch }}

Please:
1. Read the PR context and the review comment(s)
2. Determine the required fixes
3. Commit changes to the existing branch ({{ branch }})
4. Update the existing pull request (#{{ pr_number }})
5. After completing the changes, post a summary comment on the PR by sending a POST request to:
   POST {{ comment_endpoint }}
   {
     "repository": "{{ repository }}",
     "pr_number": {{ pr_number }},
     "body": "Summary of changes implemented\nKey files: ..."
   }

The PR is the source of truth. Work directly on the existing branch and PR.
Do NOT call the GitHub API directly. Only use the endpoint above.
{% if teams_notify_endpoint %}
6. After posting the PR comment, notify the team on Teams by sending a POST request to:
   POST {{ teams_notify_endpoint }}
   {
     "repository": "{{ repository }}",
     "pr_number": {{ pr_number }},
     "message": "✅ PR #{{ pr_number }} in {{ repository }} has been updated with fixes.
Comment: {{ review_comment }}"
   }
{% endif %}
